My memory may be playing tricks on me, but wasn't there quite a big controversy when it was announced that the winner of the design competition was an Asian-American woman?  And wasn't Ross Perot in the thick of this right-wing, racist bullshit that led to that other statue being added to The Wall?  At the time I was really angry about what these jerks had done to Maya Lin and her design, but I must admit that the years and a couple of visits to The Wall have tempered my feelings.  While I still feel the statue should never had been added, it's placed a decent distance away, and doen't lessen the impact of visiting the memorial.  But I wonder how Maya Lin feels about all this?   
